{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_kfw7f8yhy7hp_1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: The Pattern | astrology\nURL: https://www.thepattern.com/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThe Pattern | astrology\n\ntop of page\n\nTHE PATTERN\n\nUnderstand Yourself on a Deeper Level\n\nThe Pattern is a personalized astrology app that helps you understand the patterns shaping your life and influencing your relationships.\n\nGET YOUR NATAL CHART\n\nDownload The Pattern\n\n# Your Natal Chart\n\nThe Pattern uses your birth chart information to give you deeply personal insights — without the complicated astrology language.\n\nGet Your Natal Chart\n\nYour Pattern\n\nYour Bonds\n\nYour Transits\n\nRomantic Transits\n\nTime-Travel\n\nIn-Depth\n\nShared Experienes\n\n## Your Pattern\n\nYour Pattern is a unique combination of personality traits, based on your natal chart.\n\nDOWNLOAD THE PATTERN\n\nIt offers deeper insight into yourself, your relationships, and your life.\n\nUnderstanding your Pattern can help you navigate life with greater self-awareness, compassion, and clarity.\n\n### What's Your Pattern? SUBSCRIBE TO OUR NEWSLETTER\n\nGet insights and updates to help you get more out of The Pattern.\n\nbottom of page\n\n---\n\nTitle: The Pattern App: Features, Pricing, Readings, & More\nURL: https://www.bustle.com/life/pattern-app-review-features-price\nPublished: 2024-05-15T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThe Pattern app has become a go-to download for astro girlies, but it’s also a fave amongst the skeptics, like your friend who rolls their eyes whenever you mention you’re a Libra. The app uses your birth chart to come up with personalized info that can help you feel seen and understood and it also offers insight that has been described as “scarily accurate”— and that’s what seems to win everyone over.\n[...]\nFrom Your Pattern, to Your Timing, to Your Chart, there’s so much to read, listen to, and learn based on the planetary cycles, which is why I knew I had to try it. While the app has been around since 2017, it’s always adding new features and snagging new fans, including yours truly.\n[...]\nLike many astrology apps, The Pattern presents you with your birth chart, which shows your sun, moon, and rising signs, other planetary placements, and what it all means. From there, it dives deeper into your unique personality traits so you can better understand how you think and act. You can also enter other people’s birthdays to see how well you connect.\n[...]\nthe app,\n[...]\nplanetary cycles influencing\n[...]\ncompatibility with others, whether in a friendship or romantic sort of way.\n[...]\nTo test your compatibility, you can search for their profile within the app or create a Custom Profile. The first customized profile is free and then you can buy three more for $9.99. The app also has a whole host of Library Collections or audio episodes about planetary aspects, New Moon Guides, and other tidbits of info so you can become an astro whiz.\n[...]\nIf you want to go even deeper,\n[...]\nat your past planetary transits as well as what’s coming up\n[...]\nTime Travel feature.\n[...]\na World Timing section, too, that highlights planetary cycles that’ll affect everyone collectively.\n[...]\nThe app also helps you discover your Romantic Patterns, so you can find your best connections while also noting the challenges that might arise in your love life. If you’re still searching for your person, there’s also the Connect dating feature, which utilizes The Pattern’s algorithm to help you find love.\n[...]\nThis is a separate account within the app that allows you to upload a profile pic and bio. When you upgrade to Connect+, you get unlimited “likes” to send to others, five Super Connects to send each week to the people you like most, Bonds and other info about your compatibility, and access to a secure chat.\n[...]\nLuckily, there’s still plenty to see on the free version of the app. Another nice perk is the Time Travel feature, which allows you to plug in an exact date to see what transits will be happening then. This is ideal if you want to hold off on starting something new, like a project.\n\n---\n\nTitle: ‎The Pattern: Astrology App - App Store\nURL: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/the-pattern-astrology/id1071085727\nPublished: 2024-07-08T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: nighttimewanderlust\nHighlights:\nfeel seen and understood\n[...]\nA homegrown labor of love, The Pattern was born out of our founder’s personal journey of self-discovery. While trying to make sense of a challenging time, she recognized what an incredibly empowering tool our birth charts can be and sought to develop an application that could offer this information in a way that was easily digestible for all. Offering a psychological blueprint of one’s self and insight into the unique things they may be experiencing during a period of time, The Pattern acts as a mirror, helping\n[...]\nto better understand yourself and others,\n[...]\non a much deeper level.\n[...]\nfeatured in Vanity Fair, Time, TechCrunch, Vogue, Bustle, Mashable, Harper’s Bazaar, among others. For\n[...]\nto commonly asked\n[...]\nI have loved this app for many years and found it super insightful and helpful. I do agree with the other reviewers that the newest interface isn’t the most intuitive and I also miss community comments. Nevertheless, I still found it so incredibly valuable even after all the changes.Today, I opened the app and found out there was a “chat” feature…which is clearly AI. I even asked it directly to confirm and it wouldn’t give me a straight answer (it literally used the phrase “what does it matter” in its response…). I am feeling deeply wary about this especially in a time when people are experiencing AI induced psychosis (look it up) and worsening mental health since these language learning models love to people-please and feed delusions to the Nth degree. Especially in that context, mixing in astrology feels especially dangerous when we (collectively) are still trying to figure out what the ethical parameters for AI even are.This inclusion of the AI feature feels like a mindless push by the company to add it just because it is trending and flashy without much regard of how it may impact the real people who are actually using the app. It really gives just lack of care. I am disappointed…not surprised because this isn’t the first or last company that has done/will do this…I am just sad because I guess I expected better given how much I have loved this app over the years. Use with caution if you do continue using at all.\n\n---\n\nTitle: The Pattern: Astrology - Apps on Google Play\nURL: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.thepattern.app&hl=en\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nShare more of what moves you!We updated sharing in The Pattern, making it easier to send meaningful insights, moments, and reflections with more context.Shared Experiences is also back, giving you a place to join real conversations inside your insights and see how others relate to the same patterns.Be sure to turn on push notifications to stay connected and receive updates on freshly released personalized content!\n\n---\n\nTitle: The Pattern App Review 2026: Honest Look at Features, Pricing & Limits | Whisper\nURL: https://blog.whisper.day/reviews/the-pattern-review-2026/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\n### No conversational Q&A\n[...]\nThe Pattern does not have a chat feature. Like Co-Star, the relationship with the app is one-directional — the app generates content, you read it. If you want to ask a specific question and get a chart-informed answer, The Pattern cannot do that.\n[...]\nThe pricing structure is one of The Pattern’s weakest points relative to the category. $10/month for a single-system app with no chat feature and a passive content format is on the higher end. This is not a reason to avoid it — the quality of the content justifies the price for engaged users — but it is worth being clear about what you are paying for.\n[...]\n| The Pattern | The Whisper |\n| --- | --- |\n| Western astrology | ✅ (hidden) | ✅ |\n| BaZi / Four Pillars | ❌ | ✅ |\n| Nine Star Ki | ❌ | ✅ |\n| Vedic / Jyotish | ❌ | ✅ |\n| I Ching | ❌ | ✅ |\n| Total systems | 1 (translated) | Up to 15 |\n| Astrological language | Hidden / translated | Available in breakdown |\n| Daily short-form content | Weak | ✅ Daily Whisper |\n| Personality depth | ✅ Strong | Chart-grounded synthesis |\n| Relationship compatibility | ✅ Strong | ✅ Available |\n| Conversational AI Q&A | ❌ | ✅ Paid tiers |\n| Free tier | Partial | ✅ Available |\n| Price (paid) | ~$10/month | $4.99 / $12.99/month |\n[...]\nThe Pattern and The Whisper are serving different versions of the same underlying need: what does my chart tell me about how to navigate my life? The Pattern answers that question through deep psychological profiling in plain language. The Whisper answers it through daily synthesis across multiple independent traditions, with the underlying systems visible when you want them.\n[...]\nThe Pattern built something genuinely distinctive: a birth chart tool that makes astrological insight accessible to people who would otherwise never engage with it. The writing quality is high, the personality profiling is specific, and the relationship compatibility feature is among the best in the category. For users who want psychological depth without astrological vocabulary, The Pattern is the best-designed option available.\n[...]\nThe honest limits are scope and format. It does one system, in one voice, at a passive reading pace. The $29.99/3-month price is harder to justify for casual users than for those who engage with the depth consistently. And if you have used it long enough to absorb the core profile content, the question “what else should I know about myself?” requires a different kind of tool — one that can show you what BaZi sees, what Nine Star Ki tracks, what I Ching draws for today, and how all of those independent frameworks relate."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2d2c5eed-ceb0-4ca3-859c-ea2024b87ba2","uuid":"a689f9a2-a433-48f5-a2a5-809afa42b859","timestamp":"2026-06-10T18:31:15.985Z","tool_use_result":[{"type":"text","text":"Title: The Pattern | astrology\nURL: https://www.thepattern.com/\nPublished: N/A\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThe Pattern | astrology\n\ntop of page\n\nTHE PATTERN\n\nUnderstand Yourself on a Deeper Level\n\nThe Pattern is a personalized astrology app that helps you understand the patterns shaping your life and influencing your relationships.\n\nGET YOUR NATAL CHART\n\nDownload The Pattern\n\n# Your Natal Chart\n\nThe Pattern uses your birth chart information to give you deeply personal insights — without the complicated astrology language.\n\nGet Your Natal Chart\n\nYour Pattern\n\nYour Bonds\n\nYour Transits\n\nRomantic Transits\n\nTime-Travel\n\nIn-Depth\n\nShared Experienes\n\n## Your Pattern\n\nYour Pattern is a unique combination of personality traits, based on your natal chart.\n\nDOWNLOAD THE PATTERN\n\nIt offers deeper insight into yourself, your relationships, and your life.\n\nUnderstanding your Pattern can help you navigate life with greater self-awareness, compassion, and clarity.\n\n### What's Your Pattern? SUBSCRIBE TO OUR NEWSLETTER\n\nGet insights and updates to help you get more out of The Pattern.\n\nbottom of page\n\n---\n\nTitle: The Pattern App: Features, Pricing, Readings, & More\nURL: https://www.bustle.com/life/pattern-app-review-features-price\nPublished: 2024-05-15T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: N/A\nHighlights:\nThe Pattern app has become a go-to download for astro girlies, but it’s also a fave amongst the skeptics, like your friend who rolls their eyes whenever you mention you’re a Libra. The app uses your birth chart to come up with personalized info that can help you feel seen and understood and it also offers insight that has b