 send each week to the people you like most, Bonds and other info about your compatibility, and access to a secure chat.\n[...]\nLuckily, there’s still plenty to see on the free version of the app. Another nice perk is the Time Travel feature, which allows you to plug in an exact date to see what transits will be happening then. This is ideal if you want to hold off on starting something new, like a project.\n\n---\n\nTitle: ‎The Pattern: Astrology App - App Store\nURL: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/the-pattern-astrology/id1071085727\nPublished: 2024-07-08T00:00:00.000Z\nAuthor: nighttimewanderlust\nHighlights:\nfeel seen and understood\n[...]\nA homegrown labor of love, The Pattern was born out of our founder’s personal journey of self-discovery. While trying to make sense of a challenging time, she recognized what an incredibly empowering tool our birth charts can be and sought to develop an application that could offer this information in a way that was easily digestible for all. Offering a psychological blueprint of one’s self and insight into the unique things they may be experiencing during a period of time, The Pattern acts as a mirror, helping\n[...]\nto better understand yourself and others,\n[...]\non a much deeper level.\n[...]\nfeatured in Vanity Fair, Time, TechCrunch, Vogue, Bustle, Mashable, Harper’s Bazaar, among others. For\n[...]\nto commonly asked\n[...]\nI have loved this app for many years and found it super insightful and helpful. I do agree with the other reviewers that the newest interface isn’t the most intuitive and I also miss community comments. Nevertheless, I still found it so incredibly valuable even after all the changes.Today, I opened the app and found out there was a “chat” feature…which is clearly AI. I even asked it directly to confirm and it wouldn’t give me a straight answer (it literally used the phrase “what does it matter” in its response…). I am feeling deeply wary about this especially in a time when people are experiencin